11.2 Header and body
The basic structure of an MEI document conists of two major parts, the head and the music, roughly corresponding to metadata describing the source and the music ‘itself’, respectively.
&lt;mei meiversion="5.0"&gt;
  &lt;meiHead&gt;
  &lt;!-- metadata goes here --&gt;
  &lt;/meiHead&gt;
  &lt;music&gt;
  &lt;!-- description of musical text goes here --&gt;
  &lt;/music&gt;
&lt;/mei&gt;
